# IP-Subnet

This is a simple tool that unmasks a network ID, returns the IP class and total number
of IP addresses available within a particular subnet mask.

usage: ip_subnet.py [-h]
                    [-i IP_AND_SUBNETMASK IP_AND_SUBNETMASK | -c EXTENDED_NETWORK_PREFIX | --version]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i IP_AND_SUBNETMASK IP_AND_SUBNETMASK
                        Accepts an ip adress with subnet mask in subnet
                        notation ip_subnet -i 255.255.255.0
  -c EXTENDED_NETWORK_PREFIX
                        Accepts subnet mask in extended prefix notation. i.e
                        192.168.0.22/24
  --version             show program's version number and exit

